---
The Wizard's Keep is a post-catastrophe containment school built to train arcanists without repeating the Spirebound Conclave's abuses.
Founded after Conclave revelations about prisoner experimentation.

Guiding doctrine: arcane competence should be reproducible by institution, not dependent on secretive masters.
No unsupervised field trials. No off-ledger apprentices. No research wing beyond posted watch distance. Every adept tied to a legal witness chain.

The Keep balances three incompatible mandates: instruction (produce competent practitioners), custody (control dangerous knowledge), and deniability (hide methods that would trigger intercity panic).

That balance is visibly failing. Bricked-over doors, burned archives, unfinished passages, and magically-bound personnel mark fracture lines.
Runed doors require keyword authorization. Lobby loops separate traffic classes. Sealed side doors hide quietly erased wings.

The Burnt Records Incident: focused fire damage on concealed shelving and paper stores. Institutionally sanctioned deletion, not panic destruction.

Behind the formal northern lock lies an obsidian corridor terminating at a blank wall with a circular groove: a removed or disabled mechanism. A former deep-access interface, intentionally decommissioned. In rumor it is called "the road that used to continue." Officially it does not exist.
